## üéØ Clinical Applications

### Primary Pattern & Manifestations
**Pattern**: Blood deficiency with liver-spleen disharmony and dampness
**Key Symptoms**: Abdominal pain during pregnancy, irregular menstruation, lower abdominal pain, bloating, edema, poor appetite, fatigue, mood swings, dizziness
**Tongue**: Pale with white coating
**Pulse**: Weak and wiry, or weak and slippery

### Secondary Applications
- Pregnancy-related abdominal pain
- Premenstrual syndrome (PMS)
- Functional uterine bleeding
- Chronic pelvic pain
- Irritable bowel syndrome in women
- Chronic fatigue with digestive issues

### Modern Clinical Uses
- Pregnancy complications and morning sickness
- Menstrual disorders and dysmenorrhea
- Chronic pelvic inflammatory disease
- Functional gastrointestinal disorders
- Chronic fatigue syndrome in women
- Anxiety and depression in women

## üìù Therapeutic Actions
